13/01/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- The ongoing hunger strike among prison inmates claimed its 64th victim Sunday (12 January). Ozlem Turk, 27, died in Ankara after fasting for 471 days. She was serving a 15-year sentence for being a member of the left-wing Revolutionary People's Liberation Party Front. Turkey has been criticised by the EU for living conditions in prisons and violations of inmate human rights. (Anadolu Agency, AFP - 12/01/03)
